cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with generative modelling of 2D tree skeletons, which is a problem in computer vision and graphics. The proposed network architecture is based on combining a variational autoencoder using Recurrent Neural Networks and a convolutional discriminator, which are commonly used in computer vision and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses error metrics and training procedures, which are related to machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely sub-categories as well. The paper also deals with generating complex structures, which is related to computer graphics, making cs.GR (Computer Graphics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks and deep learning techniques suggests that cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also a possible sub-category.
